<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1607,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1503125479" collectionCode="MCZ" country="United States of America" county="Central America." location="Kirejtshuk" municipality="Parsons" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" specimenCount="1" typeStatus="holotype">
<taxonomicName box="[151,366,1677,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Nitops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigrovittatus">
<emphasis box="[151,366,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Nitops nigrovittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is hereby placed in synonymy with 
<taxonomicName authority="Reitter, 1873" authorityName="Reitter" authorityYear="1873" box="[781,1148,1677,1700]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Nitops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[781,974,1677,1700]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Nitops mexicanus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter" box="[992,1140,1677,1700]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" refString="Reitter, E. (1873) Systematische Eintheilung der Nitidularian. Ferhandlungen des naturforschenden Fereines in Brunn, 12, 5 - 194." type="journal article" year="1873">Reitter, 1873</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. This placement was first proposed by Parsons in correspondence recently found in the 
<collectionCode box="[803,864,1712,1735]" country="USA" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:33791" name="Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">MCZ</collectionCode>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirejtshuk" box="[874,1064,1712,1735]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" refString="Kirejtshuk, A. G. (1997) New Palearctic nitidulid beetles, with notes on synonomy and systematic position of some species (Coleoptera: Nitidulidae). Zoosystematica Rossica, 6, 255 - 268." type="journal article" year="1997">
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:DB6C0252FFFBFFA3B5C9F9E7F9BF4B21:561AE59FFFFBFFA3B634F910F9B64A92" box="[874,986,1712,1735]" country="United States of America" county="Central America." municipality="Parsons" name="Kirejtshuk" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Kirejtshuk</location>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
also referred to this possible status change, however he represented the issue with a “?” in his publication denoting uncertainty about the status of the species. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:DB6C0252FFFBFFA3B5C9F9E7F9BF4B21:561AE59FFFFBFFA3B5ADF955FB704B59" box="[243,284,1781,1804]" country="United States of America" county="Central America." municipality="Parsons" name="The" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">The</location>
junior name has been used in recent work (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Torres" box="[804,935,1781,1804]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" refString="Torres, H. H. (2013) Escarabajos de la savia (Coleoptera: Nitidulidae) de Coahuila, Mexico. Master's thesis. Universidad Autonoma Agraria, Buenavista, Saltillo, Coahuila, 102 pp." type="book" year="2013">Torres 2013</bibRefCitation>
) and persists as the principal determination in museums in 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:DB6C0252FFFBFFA3B5C9F9E7F9BF4B21:561AE59FFFFBFFA3B47BF8B8FBA04B7A" box="[293,460,1816,1839]" country="United States of America" county="Central America." municipality="Parsons" name="North America" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">North America</location>
, thereby demonstrating the need for clarification. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:DB6C0252FFFBFFA3B5C9F9E7F9BF4B21:561AE59FFFFBFFA3B6A7F8B8FE4F4B7A" box="[1017,1059,1816,1839]" country="United States of America" county="Central America." municipality="Parsons" name="The" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">The</location>
examination of 
<typeStatus box="[1243,1289,1816,1839]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">type</typeStatus>
material and specimens identified by 
<collectingMunicipality box="[423,506,1850,1873]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Parsons</collectingMunicipality>
later in his career agree with the proposed change. 
<taxonomicName box="[1095,1287,1850,1873]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Nitops" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="294" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanus">
<emphasis box="[1095,1287,1850,1873]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Nitops mexicanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a variable species ranging from the southwest 
<collectingCountry box="[533,676,1885,1908]" name="United States of America" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">United States</collectingCountry>
south into 
<collectingCounty box="[795,979,1885,1908]" pageId="1" pageNumber="294">Central America.</collectingCounty>
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
